column4: Butterworth Spengler Conditional Jockeys' Handicap Hurdle (Challenger Stayers' Hurdle Series Qual)
column19: The lightly raced 6yo HEATHER HONEY won three in a row over 2m7f earlier in the year and she's the pick now up in trip.
column20: 9/2 Doc McCoy,  Kikijo, 6/1 Pounding Poet,  Icare Allen, 7/1 Ernest Gray,  Heather Honey, 10/1 Lihyan,  Lipa K, 14/1 My Bobby Dazzler, 20/1 Asa, 25/1 Pyramid Place, 33/1 The Jam Man
column32: Royal Arch Racing Pp & Gary Campbell
column36: Nine-time hurdle winner but struggling earlier this year; has rejoined Harriet Dickin
column37: Nine-time hurdle winner (including here for Harriet Dickin) who is below his last winning mark but struggled in the first half of this year for Olly Murphy; went through the sales ring for £13,500 in May and has plenty to prove, including stamina, on his first start since rejoining this trainer.

column19: The lightly raced 6yo HEATHER HONEY won three in a row over 2m7f earlier in the year and she's the pick now up in trip.
column20: 9/2 Doc McCoy,  Kikijo, 6/1 Pounding Poet,  Icare Allen, 7/1 Ernest Gray,  Heather Honey, 10/1 Lihyan,  Lipa K, 14/1 My Bobby Dazzler, 20/1 Asa, 25/1 Pyramid Place, 33/1 The Jam Man
column32: Hft Limted And P J King And Son
column36: In good form in this visor in the summer and could be in the mix after a two-month break
column37: Won with this visor back on at Uttoxeter (2m7f, good) in July and went close at Cartmel (3m1f, good) the following month; versatile ground-wise and can be in the mix if continuing the good work after a two-month break.
